                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/517.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to Haiti</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President of Haiti and the Minister for Foreign Affairs assure me that they
                    are doing everything possible to maintain neutrality of Haitian officials as to
                    Dominican revolutionary movement, and that no more can be done without
                    reenforcing their frontier forces, which is objected to by the Dominican
                    Minister, who has been requested to suggest a method of closer cooperation
                    between the Haitian Government and the Dominican officials.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
